HEADWORD: maraschino cherry
<hw>ma`ra*schi"no cher"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A cherry which is colored a deep red and sweetened by cooking in
colored syrup, and flavored with maraschino. It is used as a garnish in
deserts and cocktails.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The <er>marasca cherry</er> tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marasmius</ent>⟦br⟧
